 <title>Petrol engine (spark-ignition)</title>
 <definition>
  <definitionText>A petrol engine (known as a gasoline engine in American English) is an internal
      combustion engine with spark-ignition, designed to run on petrol (gasoline) and similar
      volatile fuels.</definitionText>
  <definitionSource>
